    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I think the parts that can be reused are public API parts like `Style.format`, `Styler.render`, `Styler.apply` and `Styler.applymap`. That gives you iteration logic over every row, and every column in each row, including the style information attached to that item. Also the export / use functionality. Those items could be put in a base class pretty easily I think.\n\nOther than that it'd be up to the subclass to implement\n- the template (I don't think there's much that could be inherited from a base template), which wouldn't be terrible.\n- the `_translate` method, which would be the bulk of the work\n- Any builtin styles (like `.highlight_max`)\n"
  },
