    "body": "I've pushed a branch [here](https://github.com/TomAugspurger/pandas/commits/refactor-style) sketching out what the start of the refactor might look like.\n- [HTMLStyler](https://github.com/TomAugspurger/pandas/commit/1105551377c7fbc890fa4c00d5a5a6f81d4e7539)\n- [BaseStyler and load templates from file](https://github.com/TomAugspurger/pandas/commit/76e058837285203a1b30f66ad4615f581bc1aa7c)\n- [Start LaTeX Template](https://github.com/TomAugspurger/pandas/commit/33ef5e8fab2a52973fbb330a383043982bcc523e)\n\nAt this point it's worth asking whether all this is still in scope for pandas? Other than LaTeX I'd say the big one is Markdown, which wouldn't be much code, so maybe it's OK to keep in pandas.\n"
